            <th style="width:130px">IP or Domain Reputation</th>
            <th style="width:160px">Description</th>
            <th style="width:150px">Why It Matters</th>
            <th style="width:160px">Recommended Next Action</th>
        </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
    {% for idx, row in alerts_data.alerts_raw.head(10).iterrows() %}
    <tr>
        <td class="narrow">{{ loop.index }}</td>
        <td><small class="text-muted">{{ row['Alert ID'] }}</small></td>
        <td><span class="badge badge-critical">{{ row['Severity'] }}</span></td>
        <td class="wide"><strong>{{ row['Alert Name'] }}</strong></td>
        <td class="med">
            {% if 'Alert Type' in row %}
            <small class="text-muted">{{ row['Alert Type'] | truncate(35, True, '…') }}</small>
            {% else %}—{% endif %}
        </td>
        <td><small>{{ row['Alert Time'] }}</small></td>
        <td>
            {% set _risk = row['IP or Domain Reputation'] %}
            {% if _risk == 'Malicious' %}
            <span class="badge badge-critical" title="Attacker activity">{{ _risk }}</span>
            {% elif _risk == 'Negligent' %}
            <span class="badge" style="background:#e67e22;color:#fff;" title="Misconfig / weak controls">{{ _risk }}</span>
            {% elif _risk == 'Unauthorized' %}
            <span class="badge" style="background:#8e44ad;color:#fff;" title="Shadow IT / unsanctioned service">{{ _risk }}</span>
            {% else %}—{% endif %}
        </td>
        <td class="wide">{{ row['Description'] | truncate(110, True, '…') }}</td>
        <td class="wide">
            {% if 'Alert Type' in row %}{{ alert_why(row['Alert Name'], row['Alert Type']) }}
            {% else %}{{ alert_why(row['Alert Name'], '') }}{% endif %}
        </td>
        <td class="wide">
            {% if 'Alert Type' in row %}{{ alert_next(row['Alert Name'], row['Alert Type']) }}
            {% else %}{{ alert_next(row['Alert Name'], '') }}{% endif %}
        </td>
    </tr>
    {% endfor %}
    </tbody>
</table>
{% endif %}

<div class="section-summary">
    <div class="ss-title">&#9650; Risk Summary — Why Immediate Action Matters</div>
    {% if critical_alert_count > 0 %}
    <p><strong style="color:#DA291C;">{{critical_alert_count}} critical behavioral alert(s)</strong> were generated during the assessment window. FortiCNAPP critical alerts represent the highest-confidence detections — triggered only when observed activity significantly deviates from a learned behavioral baseline, or when multiple correlated signals indicate coordinated attack activity. Each unresolved alert extends attacker dwell time: the industry average is <strong style="color:white;">194 days</strong> from initial compromise to detection. Every day without investigation increases both the scope of compromise and the cost of incident response. Treat each unresolved critical alert as an active incident until proven otherwise.</p>
    {% else %}
    <p>No critical alerts were generated during the assessment window. Continue monitoring behavioral baselines and ensure FortiCNAPP policy coverage spans all active cloud accounts, regions, and workload types to maintain detection effectiveness as the environment evolves.</p>
    {% endif %}
</div>

</section>
{% endif %}

